More and more parents use tracking devices to control their children
The fear of children makes more and more people think about controlling them by GPS.
The system, originally designed for vehicle tracking, can also follow the movement of people and thus contribute, for example, to the disappearance of the nine-year-old Anička Janatková.
Currently the device has the approximate size of a lock box, but will soon be reduced to the size of a watch.
Many people were frightened by the case of missing Anička and began to inform about the means available to better protect their children.
Even at the cost of invading your privacy.
"We all try to tell ourselves that it is not a spy, but another way to reduce the possibility of a tragedy," says Petr Pilin of Macro Weil, one of the suppliers of tracking devices in the Czech market.
"I recognize that, in certain cases, such devices can be abused, for example if they are put in someone's pocket without their knowledge, but we haven't met with such cases yet."
"Most customers actually buy it for security reasons," Pilin adds.
In their opinion, children should always know what the "box" is for and how it is used in case of emergency.
Children's psychologist Dana Bočkova warns about the fact that if the child doesn't want to take it, he'll just throw it away.
"Even younger children show great creativity when they deliberately lose certain things if they want to avoid being controlled."
"Before, the parents relied heavily on the phones, but they could turn off as easily as the tracking device," Bočková says.
In your opinion, it is questionable if in case of attack such a device is really useful.
"If it is a prepared kidnapping, the author will practically always check if the child carries some kind of electronic device that can reveal his location."
"Now it's the phone."
"As the use of tracking devices expands, it will also search for them, as its sale will undoubtedly be carried out with much publicity.".
"In such cases, criminals always go one step ahead of the police," says the psychologist.
However, it adds that such devices can help in the case of an improvised attack of a pedophile.
According to Robert Čech of the RC Monitoring company, which offers tracking services for both vehicles and people, even if, after an attack, the tracking device is destroyed immediately, its presence can serve as aid.
"The device can be configured to send the position regularly after a certain period".
"If it is damaged, at least it will facilitate the last position of the person concerned."
"The most expensive devices are integrated with a tilting meter, so if the person simply rescinds and becomes mobile, the device will immediately issue a warning with the position in question," Čech says.
In your opinion, such a service can even be obtained with intelligent mobile phones with navigation, where only a special software must be installed.
The problem with the current tracking units is that for the time being it is devices with a size similar to a lock box or smaller mobile phones.
