EU changes rules for obtaining visas
Persons should visit Visa Applicants Service centres before their interview in the Consular Section; the cost will be lower and as well as waiting time.
With effect from 10 January 2011, the procedure for the processing of a visa in the United States Embassy and consulates will change.
With the new procedure, the majority of applicants should visit the Visa Applicants Service Centres (ASC) before their interview in the Consular Section.
The staff of the SCA will take the applicant's biometric information, which will be reviewed by the Consular Section before the interview.
The new procedure will have certain advantages for applicants, including:
The total cost of handling the visa will be lower, no longer will be necessary to make a payment to conclude the appointment, another payment to process the visa application and more so that the mail service will deliver the document.
The sucker will make only one single payment that will cover the three services.
The current rate will remain unchanged: the equivalent of $140 for a tourist visa, $150 for petitioned visas (including temporary workers ' visas) and $390 for traders and investors ' visas.
People wishing to renew their visa will not have to go to an interview with the Consular Officer, but will only go to the nearest CB where they will present their documents and take their fingerprints.
Because biometric information will be taken into the ASC, applicants who require a second appointment to be interviewed in the Consular Section will remain at this time less than in the past.
Similarly, those who apply for visas in the Consulates in Juárez City, Monterrey and New Laredo will no longer pay the extra service fee of $26.
For further information on the new visa application procedure, please visit the following page: http://mexico.usebassy.gov/ bulletinines/sp101201_Visas-FAQs.html
