But it is also clear that, with current technologies, it is not possible to expect to keep confidential conversations by phone.
Nothing is easier than to find out if and when a Head of State has moved on board and contacted one of the counterparts.
How can they maintain private and confidential relations in the future?
I know perfectly that, for the time being, my prediction is science fiction and, therefore, novelty, but I imagine government agents moving discreetly into diligences with uncontrollable routes, carrying messages that have been learned from memory or, like many, hiding some data written in the pockets of their shoes.
This information is then preserved, in a single copy, in locked drawers with key: in the end, the Watergate spying attempt was less successful than WikiLeaks.
